    <a data-analytics-link="river:image" href="http://www.theverge.com/2016/3/10/11189152/olympus-pen-f-review-film-digital-camera-sample-photos"><div data-chorus-optimize-field="main_image" class="p-dynamic-image vox-lazy-load" data-original="https://cdn1.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/6-PMCEXnGmbVTLDK63cEiAXRQb8=/0x0:2500x1667/400x267/cdn0.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/49040793/akrales_160309_0973_A_0210.0.0.png" data-imgkey="49040793:*:8"></div></a>

    <div class="m-entry-slot__blurb" data-native-ad-id=description><p>Humans have a hard time letting go of the past. Sometimes it's a good thing — nostalgia helps people <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2013/07/09/science/what-is-nostalgia-good-for-quite-a-bit-research-shows.html?pagewanted=all">fight loneliness</a> and can even make them more tolerant. Other times it feels like a weakness, mostly...</p></div>

      <q>
        <a data-analytics-link="river:pullquote" href="http://www.theverge.com/2016/3/10/11189152/olympus-pen-f-review-film-digital-camera-sample-photos">Nostalgia incarnate</a>
      </q>

    <span class="m-entry-admin-button " data-remote-admin-entry-type="button" data-remote-admin-entry-id="10953193"></span>

  </div>

  
  <div class="m-entry-slot chorus-optimize -has-pull-quote " data-native-ad-id=container data-chorus-optimize-id="10958075" data-chorus-optimize-module="*">

    
    

    <h3><a analytics-link="river" data-chorus-optimize-field="hed" data-native-ad-id="headline" href="http://www.theverge.com/2016/3/10/11194034/fcc-unveils-isp-privacy-proposal">FCC wants internet providers to ask your permission before sharing data</a></h3>

    <div class="m-entry-slot__meta">
    <strong><a class="author" href="http://www.theverge.com/users/Jacob%20Kastrenakes">Jacob Kastrenakes</a></strong>
    <em><span class="m-entry-slot__long-date">March 10, 2016 01:08 pm</span><span class="m-entry-slot__short-date">6 hours ago</span></em>
      <a href="http://www.theverge.com/2016/3/10/11194034/fcc-unveils-isp-privacy-proposal#comments" class="p-comment-count heat0">2</a>
</div>


    <a data-analytics-link="river:image" href="http://www.theverge.com/2016/3/10/11194034/fcc-unveils-isp-privacy-proposal"><div data-chorus-optimize-field="main_image" class="p-dynamic-image vox-lazy-load" data-original="https://cdn0.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/1GZM0BXJD2rwHkzjB_9CwS6p0u8=/0x0:4500x3000/400x267/cdn0.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/49041683/GettyImages-465169686.0.jpg" data-imgkey="49041683:*:8"></div></a>

    <div class="m-entry-slot__blurb" data-native-ad-id=description><p>The Federal Communications Commission hopes to strengthen rules around online privacy. The commission is circulating a proposal today that would require internet service providers — like Comcast, Verizon,...</p></div>

      <q>
        <a data-analytics-link="river:pullquote" href="http://www.theverge.com/2016/3/10/11194034/fcc-unveils-isp-privacy-proposal">They have too much personal data to do whatever they want</a>
